  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "https://au-api.leap.services/"
    }
  ],
  "tags": [
    {
      "name": "LEAP Host SDK Authentication",
      "description": "We now encourage vendors to use the LEAP Host SDK for authentication, as opposed to using MessageBus which is being deprecated. <p> <b>Using the SDK authentication method</b> </p> <p> The LEAP Host SDK is the preferred authentication for Visual Apps. A LEAP app often needs to call the LEAP API Gateway services. To do so, it needs to obtain a LEAP Auth token. LEAP Host SDK simplifies this process. </p>\n  ```\n  sdk.init('LEAP Auth client ID').then(() => {\n    //client Id is not required if you have provided the token in the url\n    //or you are developing a trusted app\n    \n    if (!!sdk.leapContext.authtoken) {\n      //you can check if the SDK is ready by checking if the authtoken has value\n      console.log(sdk.leapContext.authtoken);\n    }\n   });\n  ```\n<p> <b>Sending a command to the LEAP client application</b> </p> <p> A LEAP client applications (LEAP Desktop / Web / Mobile) accepts certain messages from LEAP apps and act upon them. For example, they can open a document or show a message box. The LEAP Host SDK facilitates this process by exposing a set of semantic functions through which the LEAP app can invoke. </p>\n\n  ```\n  sdk.init('LEAP Auth client ID').then(() => {\n    // open a message box in LEAP\n    sdk.system.alert({ message: 'Hello, world' });\n  \n    // open a matter\n    sdk.matter.openMatter(openMatterRequest);\n  \n    // close the app\n    sdk.system.close();\n  });\n  ```"
    },
    {
      "name": "MessageBus",
      "description": "<b>Note:</b> This service is being deprecated, in favor of the new LEAP Host SDK. Please use the above LEAP Host SDK Authentication section or head over to https://www.npmjs.com/package/@leapdev/leap-host for more information on the SDK."
    },
    {
      "name": "Accounts",
      "description": "The following feature set provides the capability to access LEAP Bank Accounts. These APIs are designed to facilitate the retrieval, addition, and modification of accounts within LEAP."
    },
    {
      "name": "Accounting",
      "description": "The following assists with settings firm accounting settings.   "
    },
    {
      "name": "Appointments",
      "description": "The following functionality allows you to create, retrieve and delete appointments. \nNote: This endpoint requires the SuperDiary feature, please refer to the superDiary flag in /api/v1/firms/{firmid}"
    },
    {
      "name": "Calendars",
      "description": "Retrieves a list of linked Outlook shared calendars available to the user. \nNote: This endpoint requires the SuperDiary feature, please refer to the superDiary flag in /api/v1/firms/{firmid}"
    },
    {
      "name": "Card Documents",
      "description": "Documents can be uploaded to LEAP and are linked to Cards. These documents can be added, updated or retrieved from a specific Card. Typically the returned Document ID is used to fetch the AWS S3 link to the binary file.\n\nUsing the following APIs will allow you to do this."
    },
    {
      "name": "Cards",
      "description": "In LEAP, contacts are referred to as Cards. These Cards contain all the information relating to a person. Cards will often be used in tandem with Matters as these two entities can be linked. \n\nCards can be linked to multiple Matters, the various APIs below will allow you to find this information along with the ability to update those Cards."
    },
    {
      "name": "CostRecovery",
      "description": "Cost Recovery refers to the process of recuperating the costs incurred by a Lawyer or Firm. \n\nThese specific APIs are designed to facilitate the viewing, addition, and modification of Cost Recovery data for individual Matters within LEAP."
    },
    {
      "name": "CreditRefund",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to view a credit refund."
    },
    {
      "name": "Definable Tables",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to add, update or delete Definable tables for matters.\n\nA Definable table, like a Card, is a collection of information pertaining to a matter. Their main difference is that a Card is generally  a person or address-based group of information, while a Definable table is not. There may be some exceptions where a Card contains an address, but under these circumstances, the addresses serve more as an \"additional information\"  rather than one of the focal points of the information collection.\n\nThird-party users of these endpoints may only update or retrieve Definable tables. There is a content team that handles the creation of Definable tables.  When you are adding a Definable table to a matter, you should be aware of the type of table you are adding. (ie: Definable Table 6 is for Property details, 9 is for Conveyancing details, 32 is for Shopping Centre details and so on)"
    },
    {
      "name": "Document Packet",
      "description": "A Document Packet in LEAP is a way of grouping a set of documents for either a Card or a Matter. These Document Packets are utilised by Document Register where you can add a document to your Document Packet."
    },
    {
      "name": "Document Register",
      "description": "The Document Register is used to record documents that are held by a Firm. From within the creation of a Document Register you can also specify the Document Packet to link it to via <b>PacketId</b>.\n\nCreate and fetch LEAP Document Register Types with the below service functionality."
    },
    {
      "name": "Documents",
      "description": "Using signed URLs, the below functionality will allow you to fetch, update and create new LEAP Documents. \n\n <b>NOTE:</b> Creating / POSTing a new document is a 2 step process; \n\n\tStep 1: Make the POST request. \n\n\tStep 2: Use the resultant `signedURL` address to upload the documents binary (using a PUT)."
    },
    {
      "name": "Emails",
      "description": "LEAP Desktop is integrated with Outlook and can send emails using the below API. These emails can also be saved to a Matter if required."
    },
    {
      "name": "Evaluate",
      "description": "For the purpose of Evaluating multiple JS paths the endpoint can provide any data available in an XML file or JS Path as long as you have the path required."
    },
    {
      "name": "Export",
      "description": "For the purpose of Exporting accounting details relating to Journals and the accounting platform used by the Firm."
    },
    {
      "name": "Fees",
      "description": "Within LEAP Fees are used to help with calculating for invoicing. There are different types of Fees and their associated details required such as Tax, Rate Per Hour, etc."
    },
    {
      "name": "Firms",
      "description": "Firms are used to group the organisations Users and Matters within LEAP. Through these APIs, you can access and modify the specific details of a firm, including updates to different branches, which represent various offices within the firm."
    },
    {
      "name": "Investment Account",
      "description": "LEAP Account Records can contain Investment Accounts. These accounts can be added via the following API calls."
    },
    {
      "name": "Interactive Invoice",
      "description": "The below functionalities will allow you to get matter & Invoice details for Interactive Invoices."
    },
    {
      "name": "Investment Money",
      "description": "The below functionalities will allow you to get and manipulate LEAP Investment Money records"
    },
    {
      "name": "Lists",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to view certain lists of LEAP data.  "
    },
    {
      "name": "Mailing",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to use endpoints for Mailing"
    },
    {
      "name": "Matters",
      "description": "The below services allow the consumer to manipulate LEAP matters.\n\nNote that each endpoint is access controlled and hence, any 401 or 403 errors could be related to consumer permissions.\n\n Please ensure to double check the response message on any errors, for details. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Notifications",
      "description": "The ability to configure and send out notifications to LEAP Desktop for either an individual or firm wide. There are a few requirements in order to utilise this service, they are as below:\n  For a genuine notification regarding a change to the matter.\n  Not be used for marketing, spam or any other communication other than related to a direct feature/action the app performed. Holiday specials, discount codes, marketing new features etc are all off the table \n  Not be “chatty” and spam the notification stream of LEAP even with “legitimate” notifications.\n  \nTo be able to use this feature you must submit a request to LEAP Support in order to be authorised.\n\n  \nThis will be used to generate a Sender ID and Topic. Once you receive the Sender ID and Topic you can now use the API."
    },
    {
      "name": "Office Invoice Adjust",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch, update and create new LEAP Invoices. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Office Invoices",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch, update and create new LEAP Invoices. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Office Journal",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch, update and create new LEAP Journals. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Office Ledgers",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch Office Ledgers. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Office Receipts",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch and create Office Receipts. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Office Payments",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch and create Office Payments. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Payment Types",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch payment types for a LEAP account."
    },
    {
      "name": "Persons",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to manipulate LEAP persons as per your requirements. "
    },
    {
      "name": "PowerMoney",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to create or get power money transactions."
    },
    {
      "name": "Precedents",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to preview from LEAP Matter Precedents. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Preferences",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch new LEAP Firm's accounting preferences. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Purchase Orders",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to retrieve & create purchase orders. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Reporting",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch a LEAP Firm's reporting. \nFor endpoints where an ID is returned, utilise GET /api/v1/reporting/getasyncrequest/{requestid} to retrieve your request response. \n### <b>Caching</b>\n\nResponse data for reporting endpoints is cached for 4 hours."
    },
    {
      "name": "Schema",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch a LEAP Firm's Schema."
    },
    {
      "name": "Semaphore",
      "description": "The following endpoints provide the capability to control (by provisioning and revoking) access to accounting transactions. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Staff",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to fetch Staff related information."
    },
    {
      "name": "Tasks",
      "description": "The below services allow the consumer to manipulate LEAP Tasks. \nNote: This endpoint requires the SuperDiary feature, please refer to the superDiary flag in /api/v1/firms/{firmid}   "
    },
    {
      "name": "Task Codes",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to manipulate LEAP Task Codes. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Tax Codes",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to manipulate LEAP Tax Codes. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Trust",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to manipulate trust payments. "
    },
    {
      "name": "TrustReceipt",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to manipulate Trust receipts. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Timesheet",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to retrieve timesheet data. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Transit Register",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to manipulate transit register transaction data. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Trust Bank Rec",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to retrieve trust bank reconciliation initialisation data. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Trust Ledger",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to retrieve trust ledger data. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Users",
      "description": "The below functionality will allow you to work with User endpoints. "
    },
    {
      "name": "Common Responses",
      "description": "Error response codes returned by the API include:\n\n  | Error Code    | Description                              |\n | :------------:|:-----------------------------------------|\n | 301           | Moved Permanently    |\n | 400           | Bad Request    |\n | 401           | Unauthorized (bad/expired bearer token)     |\n | 403           | Forbidden (check your LEAP API Key) |\n | 404           | Not Found |\n | 429           | Too Many Requests (endpoint throttling enabled, retry request) |\n | 500           | Internal Server Error |\n | 502           | Internal error unrecognized by the Gateway |\n | 503           | Service Unavailable |\n | 504           | Gateway Timeout    \n\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Notes",
      "description": "Common notes and best practices:\n\n  * Where possible; use the 'lastRowVer' parameter - this avoids re-downloading entire lists. This is typically found on GET methods where the result is a list of data.\n\n\n* Each endpoint is access controlled. Expect a 401 / 403 response when trying to access any endpoint(s) not requested and approved.\n\n\n* When accessing your LEAP Auth client provided in the Developer Console, ensure to provided the (list of) callback URL's to LEAP Developer support when ready. These are editable within the Dev Console.\n \n\n"
    }
  ],
  "components": {
    "schemas": {
      "DocumentCreate": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": [
          "deleteCode",
          "docName",
          "docTypeId",
          "fileType",
          "matterId",
          "staffInitials"
        ],
        "properties": {
          "matterId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Matter Id",
            "format": "uuid"
          },
          "docName": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Document name"
          },
          "fileType": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Extension of file (docx, pdf etc.)"
          },
          "staffInitials": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Staff initials (no longer being used) - the property has been deprecated and will be removed"
          },
          "docTypeId": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Type of file",
            "enum": [
              "document",
              "comment",
              "voiceFile"
            ]
          },
          "deleteCode": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Mark document as deleted",
            "format": "int32"
          },
          "createdDate": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Created date (any valid datetime)",
            "format": "date-time"
          },
          "attachments": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "Add any attachements to this array",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/DocumentAttachment"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "DocumentMetadata": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "clientMatterId": {
            "type": "string",
            "format": "uuid",
            "description": "Client matter identifier"
          },
          "clientDocumentId": {
            "type": "string",
            "format": "uuid",
            "description": "Client document identifier"
          },
          "clientMatterTypeId": {
            "type": "string",
            "nullable": true,
            "description": "Client matter type identifier"
          },
          "clientMatterState": {
            "type": "string",
            "nullable": true,
            "description": "Client matter state"
          },
          "clientMatterName": {
            "type": "string",
            "nullable": true,
            "description": "Client matter name"
          },
          "clientMatterFileNumber": {
            "type": "string",
            "nullable": true,
            "description": "Client matter file number"
          },
          "clientDocumentAuthorId": {
            "type": "string",
            "format": "uuid",
            "nullable": true,
            "description": "Client document author identifier"
          },
          "clientDocumentAuthorName": {
            "type": "string",
            "nullable": true,
            "description": "Client document author name"
          },
          "clientDocumentLastModified": {
            "type": "string",
            "format": "date-time",
            "nullable": true,
            "description": "Client document last modified timestamp"
          }
        }
      },
      "ErrorResp": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "Code": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Error code",
            "format": "int32"
          },
          "PropertyName": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Property name that has caused the error"
          },
          "Message": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Error message"
          },
          "MessageHeader": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Message header, if any"
          },
          "LineItemNumber": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Which line number this error occurred on"
          }
        }
      },
      "MatterAccountingJson": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "feeEstimate": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "Chargeable work-estimate",
            "format": "double"
          },
          "feeEstimateGST": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "Tax value of the fee estimate",
            "format": "double"
          },
          "disbursementsEstimate": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "Estimates on the total disbursement on the matter",
            "format": "double"
          },
          "disbursementsEstimateGST": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "Tax value of the disbursements estimate",
            "format": "double"
          },
          "showEstimateWarning": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Flag to warn the Solicitor if they are nearing the fee estimate of the matter"
          },
          "minimumCreditBalance": {
            "type": "number",
            "description": "(United States-only field); Allowable minimum credit balance for the matter (i.e. The retainer fee for the matter)",
            "format": "double"
          },
          "creditBalanceWarning": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "(United States-only) Flag to warn the Lawyer if they are close to exhausting the credit balance of the matter"
          },
          "omitFromOverdueInvoices": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Flag to exclude the particular matter from the creation of overdue invoices"
          },
          "invoiceSettings": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/InvoiceFixedJson"
          },
          "costAgreement": {
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/CostAgreementJson"
          },
          "taxFree": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Flag to determine if matter is tax-free or not"
          },
          "debtorNote": {
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Debtor comment from \"Matter Details\""
          },
          "billingMode": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Indicates whether the matter is not billable or will be billed next or later invoice cycle\nBilling Mode: -1 = Not billable | 0 = Billable next invoice | 1 = Billable later invoice",
            "format": "int32"
          },
          "legalAid": {
            "description": "(United Kingdom-only) Flags whether the matter is a Legal Aid matter or not",
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Object"
          },
          "staffFeeAllocations": {
            "description": "Allocation of fees (in percentage) for the staff who worked on the Matter",
            "$ref": "#/components/schemas/StaffFeeAllocations"
          },
          "autoAllocateFees": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Flag to determine if the fees are auto-allocated to the staff or not"
          },
          "timeRecordedMatter": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Flag to determine if the work-hours for the matter are being recorded or not"
          }
        }
      },
