          "relations": {
            "type": "array",
            "description": "Table relations as defined by the Content team\n\nTable Relations provide association of related parties and/or relevant party data by linking both Cards and/or Tables to ensure Matter Types are easier to complete.  \nThe key to using Table Relations effectively is considering if the related Table (child table) is required for every instance of the Table (parent table) where there is multiple. \n\nA simple example is relating the other side's solicitor/lawyer Table to the other side Table\n\nGenerally, integrators are not required to fill-up or update this object, as this is defined by LEAP's content team",
            "items": {
              "$ref": "#/components/schemas/RelationsJson"
            }
          },
          "extra": {
